	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;   I got my bag last night and I can say for sure that the Gnome that sells it is not in Ak'Anon anymore.  I hunted for an hour and even with my tracking skill maxed, could never pick him up that way either.  I went to Sol A and picked him up on tracking immediately.  The trip down to his little fort is long and winding.  Be prepared to clear the way of many Goblins who are agro and can see through Invis.  I cast SOW and Strength on myself before going in because my weight went from 65 to 196 stones due to the 5500 plat I was carrying.  I also wore all the Charisma items that I own to help with the price.  He charged me 5320 plat for the bag with my Charisma at 104.  Just for fun, I took off my Charisma stuff and at my base 70 Charisma, he asked 6330pp for the bag.  A whopping 1K increase in the price.<br>     As a level 51 Druid, it's real easy to do this alone, but others can if you get a friend to SOW and Strengh you.  The spells should easily last long enough to get the bag and after buying it, you're light as a feather.<br>     I love the bag and will keep all my spare heavy equipment in it, as well as all the heaviest loot.  Good Luck getting yours!<br>&nbsp;<br>StarChaser - Wood Elf Druid of the 43rd Season</td></tr>
